name: Nineteen
description:
Alice likes word "nineteen" very much. She has a string s and wants the string
to contain as many such words as possible. For that reason she can rearrange
the letters of the string. For example, if she has string
"xiineteenppnnnewtnee", she can get string "xnineteenppnineteenw", containing
(the occurrences marked) two such words. More formally, word "nineteen" occurs
in the string the number of times you can read it starting from some letter of
the string. Of course, you shouldn't skip letters. Help her to find the
maximum number of "nineteen"s that she can get in her string. Input The first
line contains a non-empty string s, consisting only of lowercase English
letters. The length of string s doesn't exceed 100. Output Print a single
integer — the maximum number of "nineteen"s that she can get in her string.
Examples Input nniinneetteeeenn Output 2 Input
nneteenabcnneteenabcnneteenabcnneteenabcnneteenabcii Output 2 Input
nineteenineteen Output 2
